function findPointTowardsSecondPoint(x1, y1, x2, y2, distance):
    // Calculate the vector from the first point to the second point
    dx = x2 - x1
    dy = y2 - y1

    // Calculate the length (magnitude) of the vector
    vector_length = square_root(dx * dx + dy * dy)

    // Normalize the vector (convert it to a unit vector)
    normalized_dx = dx / vector_length
    normalized_dy = dy / vector_length

    // Calculate the new point's coordinates
    new_x = x1 + normalized_dx * distance
    new_y = y1 + normalized_dy * distance

    return (new_x, new_y)

```
